{
  "doc_id": "33475",
  "text": "There are several limitations to this study that merit attention. First, there was a large percentage of missing data values for parents' level of education. Although this is a potential weakness, removing these variables from the analysis did not substantively change the contribution of other variables in the logistic regression models. Regardless, the validity of the findings regarding parents' level of education may be limited. Additionally, some of the data analyzed in this study were self-reported (e.g., parent's education level, student ethnicity, student age, student gender); these data were not verified. Lastly, this study did not employ an experimental design; a causal relationship between predictor variables and student retention could not be formally determined [CITATION_1] . Replication with similar findings for other populations will serve to strengthen the external validity of this study.",
